"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-biles-would-not-be-crushed-if-she-missed-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Simone Biles dropped out of multiple events at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, after suffering with the \\\"twisties\\\", a type of mental block where gymnasts are disoriented.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.1424635206743627e-13, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703097123, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  PublishedJan 11, 2024, 01:45 AM  UpdatedJan 11, 2024, 10:25 PM  NEW YORK-Simone Biles felt like a failure after the Tokyo Olympics and would not be crushed if she did not make the United States squad for Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Next_Entertainment_World\", \"score\": 0.9941566698754825, \"rank\": 0.00580079709263885, \"text\": \"NEW\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Next_Entertainment_World\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Next_Entertainment_World\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999961346, \"rank\": 2.9063835392778252e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5559229065491087, \"rank\": 0.7971508646632425, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997362465, \"rank\": 2.637260449946565e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gymnast headed to the Tokyo showpiece in 2021 eyeing a record haul of six gold medals, but returned home with just a silver and a bronze after suffering a crisis of confidence.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7846125882389569, \"rank\": 0.2745086088376968, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She dropped out of multiple events after she was hit with the \\\"twisties\\\", which is a type of mental block in which gymnasts are disoriented or feeling lost in the air, which could be dangerous.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wish I could sit here and tell you it was glorious,\\\" Biles told Vanity Fair, of her time off following the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1081, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9083471797489278, \"rank\": 0.09190153882040974, \"text\": \"Vanity Fair\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I took a break after 2016 (Rio Olympics), I had the time of my life.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was doing anything and everything.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But after the 2020 Games, it was kind of depressing until I started therapy and got help.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt like a failure.\\\"\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a nearly two-year hiatus,she returned to competition in August 2023at the US Classic and proved that she remained the sport's dominant force, winning the all-around.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Weeks later,she won a record eighth all-around titleat the US Gymnastics Championships.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_U.S._National_Gymnastics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999743038390588, \"rank\": 2.5696821149073145e-05, \"text\": \"US Gymnastics Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_U.S._National_Gymnastics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_U.S._National_Gymnastics_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 2023's World Championships in Belgium,she won four golds, including a record-equalling sixth all-around crown.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9227022897391084, \"rank\": 0.07752761818735363, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Judging by her results, Biles should be on the US squad for the July 26-Aug 11 Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7844292030097064, \"rank\": 0.19807736120191555, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, if she is not, the four-time Olympic gold medallist said she would move on.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If I do not make it to Paris, it will not absolutely crush me,\\\" said the 26-year-old, who will feature on February's Vanity Fair cover and who was voted the Associated Press' Athlete of the Year in December.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1943, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999994499376, \"rank\": 5.50060892140787e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9083471797489278, \"rank\": 0.09190153882040974, \"text\": \"Vanity Fair\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the sacrifices she has had to make during her comeback is being away from husband and Green Bay Packers safety Jonathan Owens.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"score\": 0.9999928980971419, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonathan Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two met on a dating site andwere married last April.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking about him, it was clear that that is something she cherishes as much as gymnastics, if not more.\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Besides his looks, he was so sweet and kind, and I think what I liked about him was his confidence.\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He truly believes he's the best at everything,\\\" said Biles, who gets to many Packers games.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was 19 when I won my first Olympics, and I was like, how am I supposed to top this?\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My wedding topped it.\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the greatest feeling ever.\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are both so busy, so it's not like I am sitting (around) waiting for him to come home, but it's just hard.\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"REUTERS  Gymnastics  Olympics  United States  World championships  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5559229065491087, \"rank\": 0.7971508646632425, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2976, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": []}]}"